            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": false,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* Funding request of $9 billion for NASA's Science Mission Directorate (SMD) to maintain U.S. leadership in space exploration and discovery.\n* Supports critical roadmaps in Earth Science, Planetary Science, and Astrophysics based on nonpartisan National Academies' Decadal Survey priorities.\n* Protects the specialized aerospace workforce and scientific talent pipeline from the budget instability and personnel losses seen in prior cycles.\n* Enables the U.S. to set 21st-century exploration norms and remain competitive with rapidly expanding international space programs, including China's.",
            "rationale": "This draft value uses the specific $9 billion request amount and topline advocacy talking points regarding U.S. leadership, decadal priorities, and workforce stability.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
