            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "NASA Science funding supports high-tech research and conservation in Vermont, including $1.59M in recent obligations. Notable local impacts include Isciences LLC in Burlington maintaining critical geospatial libraries, the Wildlife Management Institute in Cabot applying NASA data to biodiversity conservation, and Middlebury College conducting astrophysics research on X-ray binaries.",
            "rationale": "Drafted using specific local spending data, citing active grants for Isciences LLC, Wildlife Management Institute, and Middlebury College to demonstrate diverse regional benefits.",
