            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* NASA Science invested $1,591,148 in VT-00 (FY23-25), supporting local jobs and academic research at Middlebury College and the University of Vermont.\n* Isciences LLC in Burlington ($266,448) maintains the GDAL geospatial library, a global standard for satellite data processing and environmental monitoring.\n* The Wildlife Management Institute in Cabot ($200,303) applies NASA Earth Science data to critical biodiversity and landscape conservation research.\n* These programs provide a steady demand for Vermont's technical workforce, including contract work performed by Concepts Nrec, LLC ($220,367).",
